02/03/2011
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Thousands of army retirees joined a march in Bucharest on Tuesday (March 1st) to protest government austerity measures that cut their pensions.
The demonstrators walked about 3km from the Military Academy to the government headquarters, diverting trafficking.
A lawsuit filed by the retirees against the government will be heard on March 23rd.
(Adevarul, Ziare, Realitatea - 01/03/11)
